               <p>WILLIAM BROWN. I am a <rs id="t18300415-348-viclabel1883" type="occupation">linen-draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-348-victim2870 t18300415-348-viclabel1883"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18300415-348-crimeloc1884">Beech-street, Barbican</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-348-crimeloc1884" type="placeName" value="Beech-street, Barbican"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-348-crimeloc1884" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-348-off1881 t18300415-348-crimeloc1884"></join>. On the 20th of February, about half-past five o'clock, I saw these handkerchiefs full two feet within the door; and about six I heard a bustle in the street, went out, and the prisoner was brought to my door with the handkerchiefs in his possession - I did not see them taken; I am certain of them - they have my shopmark on them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-348-person2871">
                  FREDERICK 
                  PITE
               <interp inst="t18300415-348-person2871" type="surname" value="PITE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-348-person2871" type="given" value="FREDERICK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-348-person2871" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a hatter, and live opposite to Mr. Brown. About half-past six o'clock I saw the prisoner, with a companion, lurking about Mr. Brown's door- I saw the prisoner take a piece of print, as I thought, from inside the door, and conceal it under his coat; I followed, and took him about four doors off with it under his coat - I also collared the other, but he struggled and got from me; he was taken at the end of the street again, but was afterwards rescued.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-348-person2872">
                  JOHN 
                  PARRY
               <interp inst="t18300415-348-person2872" type="surname" value="PARRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-348-person2872" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-348-person2872" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was on duty as patrol, and received the prisoner in charge.</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written Defence, stating that three boys ran by him, and dropped the goods, which he picked up, and was immediately taken.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-348-person2873">
                  FREDERICK 
                  PITE
               <interp inst="t18300415-348-person2873" type="surname" value="PITE"></interp>
